<item>
            <title>[HBASE-11970] BlockCache would be instantiated when Master doesn&apos;t host regions</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-11970</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;HMaster ctor calls HRegionServer ctor which calls CacheConfig ctor where CacheConfig.instantiateBlockCache() would create BlockCache.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This happens even if Master is configured not to host regions.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This was observed when I tried to answer question from the thread titled:&lt;br/&gt;
&apos;The default hbase.regionserver.info.port doesn&apos;t work&apos;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12741227">HBASE-11970</key>
            <summary>BlockCache would be instantiated when Master doesn&apos;t host regions</summary>
