                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14132469" author="mantonov" created="Sat, 13 Sep 2014 02:10:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Aren&apos;t meta table region (if co-located) blocks cached in here?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14132473" author="yuzhihong@gmail.com" created="Sat, 13 Sep 2014 02:18:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;BlockCache is allocated even if hbase:meta is not collocated with master. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14132477" author="mantonov" created="Sat, 13 Sep 2014 02:19:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Ah,i see. I thought you were referring to the case when master does not host user regions, but serves meta.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14134100" author="jxiang" created="Mon, 15 Sep 2014 16:42:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Good catch. Is the mem pre-allocated at the cache instantiation?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14134108" author="yuzhihong@gmail.com" created="Mon, 15 Sep 2014 16:49:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The memory would be reserved for BlockCache.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The point is, BlockCache shouldn&apos;t be instantiated when master is configured not to host any region.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14134143" author="jxiang" created="Mon, 15 Sep 2014 17:13:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is a little confusing. Sorry for that.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It is not &quot;master is configured not to host any region&quot;. Instead, it is something like &quot;master is not configured to host regions if there are other regionservers&quot;. For example, in standalone/pseudo-distributed mode, only one node is brought up by default, and the master has all regions.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14134146" author="yuzhihong@gmail.com" created="Mon, 15 Sep 2014 17:17:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The scenario this issue is concerned is not single node deployment.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14134156" author="jxiang" created="Mon, 15 Sep 2014 17:25:21 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;The memory would be reserved for BlockCache.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;So, is the memory not usable for other purpose any more? It would not be a concern if some a tiny resouce is wasted.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;The scenario this issue is concerned is not single node deployment.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;That&apos;s right.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14134418" author="ndimiduk" created="Mon, 15 Sep 2014 20:19:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Master is only hosting system tables in the new architecture, correct? I would suggest only using LruBlockCache for such a context.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14150211" author="jxiang" created="Fri, 26 Sep 2014 23:37:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed this in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-12034&quot; title=&quot;If I kill single RS in branch-1, all regions end up on Master!&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-12034&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-12034&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. For master that doesn&apos;t host any region, block cache is not instantiated.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
